   <learningOverviewbody>
      <lcIntro>
         <p>What might seem to work well when using conrefs in English content might not work well
            when the content is translated. Here are a few guidelines that you will understand after
            completing this lesson: </p>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <p>Donâ€™t use conref with ph to replace parts of a sentence.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p>Use extreme caution when using conref to reuse whole sentences.
               </p>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p>When you do conref, do it with whole block elements that meet
                  the following requirements: <ul>
                     <li>
                        <p>The reused content is grammatically independent.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>The referenced element and referencing element are
                           within the same context.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ul>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </lcIntro>
